==Ainu==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|ain|/an/}}

===Etymology 1===
Possibly a [[shortened]] form of [[anihi]]. It may also have come directly from the verb [[an]] (to [[be]], to [[exist]]).

===Pronoun===
{{ain-pron|l|{{ain-kana-conv|„Ç¢„É≥}}}}

# {{lb|ain|[[indefinite]] [[pronoun]]}}  [[someone]], [[somebody]]. An undetermined or unspecified [[person]] or [[thing]]. It can also refer to someone whose identity is clear from the context.
#: {{syn|ain|a|sinuma|asinuma|anihi}}
#: {{usex|ain|Cis-'''an'''.|'''Someone''' is crying.}}
#: {{usex|ain|Asinuma akar sinot-'''an'''.|'''We'''‚Äôre playing.}} 
#: {{usex|ain|Pirka-'''an'''.|'''You‚Äôre''' beautiful.}}
#: {{usex|ain|Aynu ray-an.|'''The person''' is dying.}}

===Usage notes===
*'''-an''', no matter the context, is only used with [[intransitive]] verbs.
*'''-an''' may act as an [[emphasizing]] pronoun, emphasizing what is doing the action. This may lead to situations where the context is ambiguous, since the verb could be in the passive voice. In example four, it can mean ‚Äú'''The person''' is dying‚Äù or ‚Äú'''The person is being killed'''.‚Äù
* '''-an''' may be often used as an [[inclusive]] first-person pronoun ([[we]]) as well as a [[respectful]] second-person pronoun. See examples two and three.

===Etymology 2===
Similar to {{cog|ja|-}} {{ja-r|„ÅÇ„Çã}}.

===Verb===
{{ain-verb|l|{{ain-kana-conv|„Ç¢„É≥}}}}

# {{lb|ain|intransitive|copulative}} to [[exist]], [[be]] (somewhere); [[there is]]
#: {{usex|ain|Aynu '''an''' [[ruwe ne]].|'''There is''' an Ainu.}}

===Particle===
{{ain-verb|l|{{ain-kana-conv|„Ç¢„É≥}}}}

# (Emphatic [[particle]]) A final particle used to emphasize or reinforce a statement.; it is equivalent to Japanese [[„Çà]].
#: {{usex|ain|Poronno opotuyep ki okake, k-askeikre arka humi '''an'''.|My fingers '''really''' hurt after typing a lot.}}

====See also====
* {{l|ain|ne||to be}}

