==Bikol Central==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|bcl|ang}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{bcl-IPA}}

===Etymology 1===
From Proto-Central Philippine ''*a≈ã''. Cognate with {{cog|ceb|ang}}, {{cog|hil|ang}}, {{cog|tl|ang}}, {{cog|war|an}}.

Further etymology is debated; some have theorized a relationship to {{cog|poz-pro|*a||direct marker}}, from {{cog|map-pro|*a||direct marker}} with the addition of an unclear nasal suffix. Compare {{cog|pam|ing}}.

====Particle====
{{bcl-head|particle|b=+}}

# {{n-g|direct marker for all general nouns other than personal proper nouns}}
#: {{ux|bcl|Nagdalagan '''an''' lalaki pasiring sa baybayon.|'''The''' man ran towards the shore.}}
#: {{ux|bcl|Kinakan kan ikos '''an''' sira. (Naga)|-}} {{ux|bcl|Kinaon kan ikos '''an''' sira. (Legazpi)|The cat ate '''the''' fish.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* This particle is analyzed as the definite article (i.e., ''the'') when used alone, and the indefinite article (i.e., ''a'' or ''an'') when used with the numeral "''[[saro]]''".
*: {{ux|bcl|'''An''' saldang. (Naga)|-}}
*: {{ux|bcl|'''An''' aldaw. (Legazpi)|'''The''' sun.}}
*: {{ux|bcl|'''An sarong''' tawo.|'''A''' person.}}
* Specific nouns are marked with "[[si]]" or "[[su]]".
* Direct personal proper nouns (''primarily names'') are marked with "[[si]]".

===Etymology 2===

====Pronoun====
{{bcl-head|pronoun|'an|b=+}}

