==German==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|de|gmh|ane|an(e)}}, from {{inh|de|goh|ana}}, from {{inh|de|gmw-pro|*ana}}, from {{inh|de|gem-pro|*ana}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|de|/an/|[ îan]}}
** {{audio|de|De-an2.ogg|a=<<Germany>> (<<Berlin>>)}}
** {{audio|de|De-an.ogg}}
** {{rhymes|de|an|s=1}}
* A lengthened form {{IPAchar|/aÀên/}} is possible in non-prepositional uses, e.g. in the prefix {{m|de|an-}} or the adverb {{m|de|daran}}. This was formerly widespread, but is now chiefly restricted to Austria and Switzerland (where it is optional). Compare similarly the distinction between {{m|de|in}} and {{m|de|ein-}}.
<!--Claim in DWB that this has always been restricted to Upper German is wrong. See RhWb for Rhenish, WestfWb for Low German, Adelung for EastCG.-->

===Preposition===
{{head|de|preposition}} {{+obj|de|dat}}

# {{lb|de|local}} [[on]], [[upon]], [[at]], [[in]], [[against]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Das Bild h√§ngt '''an''' der Wand.|The picture hangs '''on''' the wall.}}
# [[by]], [[near]], [[close]] to, [[next]] to
# {{lb|de|temporal|with days or times of day}} [[on]]; [[in]]; [[at]]
#: {{ux|de|Wir treffen uns am ('''an''' dem) Dienstag.|We're meeting '''on''' Tuesday.}}
#: {{ux|de|Ich werde sie am ('''an''' dem) Abend sehen.|I will see her '''in''' the evening.}}
# {{lb|de|temporal}} [[a]], [[per]], {{ng|only used with the word {{m|de|Tag||day}}, otherwise use {{m|de|in}}}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|zweimal '''am''' Tag|twice '''a''' day}}

{{head|de|preposition}} {{+obj|de|acc}}

# [[on]], [[onto]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Ich h√§nge das Bild '''an''' die Wand.|I hang the picture '''on''' the wall.}}
# [[at]], [[against]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Schauen Sie '''an''' die Tafel.|Look '''at''' the blackboard.}}
# [[to]], [[for]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Ein Brief '''an''' Anna.|A letter '''for''' Anna.}}

{{head|de|preposition}} {{+obj|de|dat/acc}}

# {{lb|de|any relation to an object or attribute regardless of time and space}} [[of]], [[on]], [[in]], [[for]], [[about]]
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|'''an''' einem Roman schreiben|to write '''on''' a novel}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Mangel '''an''' Lebensmitteln|lack '''of''' food}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Alle Menschen sind frei und gleich '''an''' W√ºrde und Rechten geboren|All human beings are born free and equal '''in''' dignity and rights.}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Er ist schuld '''an''' dem Ungl√ºck|He is responsible '''for''' the misfortune}}
#: {{ux|inline=1|de|Das mag ich nicht '''an''' ihm|I don't like that '''about''' him}}

====Usage notes====
* Usually used to refer to something being on a vertical surface, as opposed to {{m|de|auf}}, which usually points to a horizontal surface.
* When followed by the masculine/neuter definite article in the dative case (i.e. {{m|de|dem||the}}), the two words generally contract to {{m|de|am||on the}} if not emphasized.
* When followed by the neuter definite article in the accusative case (i.e. {{m|de|das||the}}), the two words generally contract to {{m|de|ans||on the}} if not emphasized.

====Inflection====
