### {{n-g|denoting uncertainty by itself, without a verb of doubting}}
### {{lb|la|chiefly in and after the {{l|en|Augustan}} period}} {{n-g|standing for {{m|la|sive|sƒ´ve}}}}
### {{n-g|where the first disjunctive clause is to be supplied from the general idea or where {{m|la|an}} stands for {{m|la|utrum}} or {{m|la|necne}}}}
### {{n-g|Since in such distributive sentences expressive of doubt, the opinion of the speaker or the probability usually inclines to the second, ''i.e.'' to the clause beginning with {{m|la|an}}, the expressions {{m|la|haud scio an|haud sci≈ç an}}, {{m|la|nescio an|nesci≈ç an}}, and {{m|la|dubito an|dubit≈ç an}} incline to an affirmative signification, ‚ÄúI almost know‚Äù, ‚ÄúI am inclined to think‚Äù, ‚ÄúI almost think‚Äù, ‚ÄúI might say‚Äù, ‚ÄúI might assert that‚Äù, etc., for ‚Äúperhaps‚Äù, ‚Äúprobably‚Äù.}}
### {{n-g|Sometimes the distributive clause beginning with {{m|la|an}} designates directly the opposite, the more improbable, the negative; in which case {{m|la|nescio an|nesci≈ç an}}, {{m|la|haud scio an|haud sci≈ç an}}, etc., like the English ''{{lang|en|I know not whether}}'', signify ‚ÄúI think that not‚Äù, ‚ÄúI believe that not‚Äù, etc.}}{{attention|la|Could someone who is able merge the following into the above sense structure, please?}}<!--
# {{context|introduces questions expecting negative answer or further question|lang=la}} can it be that
#: {{ux|la|'''An''' refert, ubi et in qua arrigas?|'''Does it''' make any difference to me who made you horny, or when?}}
# [[or]], [[either]]
#: {{ux|la|Vide utrum vis '''an'''...|Consider whether you want to '''or'''...}}

-->

====Usage notes====
* Used with {{m|la|utrum||whether}} in the construction {{m|la||utrum...'''an'''|whether...'''or'''}}:
*: ''Nescio quid intersit, utrum nunc veniam, '''an''' ad decem annos.''
*:: I know not what matter it is, whether I come now '''or''' after ten years.

