#*: {{quote|ang|Foresetnessa ne bƒìo√æ nƒÅhw«£r '''ƒÅna''', ac bƒìo√æ «£fre t≈ç sumum ≈ç√∞rum worde ƒ°efƒìƒ°eda.|Prepositions never occur '''by themselves''': they are always attached to some other word.}}
#* '''c. 992''', [[w:√Ülfric of Eynsham|√Ülfric]], "[https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Homilies_of_the_Anglo-Saxon_Church/XXVII The Nativity of St. Paul the Apostle]"
#*: {{quote|ang|Petrus '''ƒÅna''' spr√¶c for ealne √æone hƒìap.|Peter '''by himself''' spoke for the whole group.}}

=====Usage notes=====
In the above senses ("only" and "alone"), this word was often used in the weak declension, often indeclinably as ''ƒÅna''.

