===Etymology===
From Proto-Central Philippine ''*a≈ã''. Cognate with {{cog|ceb|ang}}, {{cog|hil|ang}}, {{cog|tl|ang}}, {{cog|bcl|an}}.

Further etymology is debated; some have theorized a relationship to {{cog|poz-pro|*a||direct marker}}, from {{cog|map-pro|*a||direct marker}} with the addition of an unclear nasal suffix. Compare {{cog|pam|ing}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{war-IPA}}

===Particle===
{{head|war|particle}}

# {{n-g|direct marker for all general nouns other than personal proper nouns}}
#: {{ux|war|Midalagan '''an''' lalaki paingon ha baybayon.|'''The''' man ran towards the shore.}}
#: {{ux|war|Gikaon han iring '''an''' isda.|The cat ate '''the''' fish.}}

====Usage notes====
* This particle is analyzed as the definite article (i.e., ''the'') when used alone, and the indefinite article (i.e., ''a'' or ''an'') when used with the numeral "''[[usa]]''" plus "ka" that quantifies an object/object that it modifies.
*: {{ux|war|'''An''' adlaw.|'''The''' sun.}}
*: {{ux|war|'''An usa''' ka tawo.|'''A''' person.}}
* Specific nouns are marked with "[[si]]".
* Direct personal proper nouns (''primarily names'') are marked with "[[si]]".

==Yola==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|yol|enm|and|an}}, from {{inh|yol|ang|and}}, {{m|ang|ond}}, {{m|ang|end}}, from {{inh|yol|gem-pro|*andi}}, {{m|gem-pro|*an√æi}}.

